{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Almond Cookies","content":["Place sugar into mixing bowl and grind <nobr>15 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>.","Add butter, egg, almond extract, vanilla, salt and flour. With aid of spatula through hole in mixing bowl lid mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Divide dough in half and shape into disks. Tightly wrap dough in cling wrap and refrigerate 1 hour. Clean mixing bowl.","Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment and set aside.","Working with half the dough at a time, roll into ¾ inch ropes. Cut into finger-like pieces (approx. 46 total). Use a toothpick to mark 3 lines for the \"knuckles\". At one end of each piece, apply pressure to form the nail bed cavity. Place on prepared baking sheet (approx. 1 in. apart) and bake for 12-18 minutes (350°F), or until lightly browned and cooked through. Allow to cool 5 minutes before placing on cooling rack to cool completely."]},{"title":"Decoration","content":["Place grape jelly into mixing bowl and heat <nobr>3 min\/195°F\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Dip almond slices into jelly and place on fingernail cavity. Let set for 2 hours before serving. Store in an airtight container."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Almond Cookies","content":["4 ½ oz sugar","8 oz unsalted butter, room temperature","1 large egg","1 tsp almond extract              (optional)","1 tsp vanilla extract","1 pinch salt","14 oz all-purpose flour"]},{"title":"Decoration","content":["7 oz grape jelly","46 sliced almonds"]}],"id":"r108715","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-Q-o-aq2s22I\/XZWfgcKST9I\/AAAAAAAAfFo\/nN-2mjiHkugHtidZy7l5ww9WZ41hSyOYACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_w95TIScYpR_cz3_3.png","title":"Witches' Finger Cookies","publishedAt":"2017-10-13T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1 g","fat":"4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"13 g","calories":"393 kJ \/ 94 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling wrap, parchment paper, toothpick, cooling rack, airtight container, baking sheet, refrigerator, oven","hintsAndTricks":["For a gluten-free version: replace all-purpose flour with gluten-free flour.","Coconut flakes can be used to replace almonds for fingernails. Break or cut large coconut flakes into nail shapes.","For a truly ghoulish cookie: lightly dip the end opposite the 'fingernail' into the hot jelly and place back onto baking sheet. Drizzle remaining jelly over fingers to look like blood splatter. Let set for 2 hours before serving.","Use 2 tsp of vanilla extract if desired, when not using almond extract.","Replace grape jelly with strawberry, mixed berry or another similarly colored jelly.","If jelly sets before you have time to complete decorating, just reheat remaining jelly in mixing bowl <strong>2 min\/195°F\/speed 1<\/strong>.","Use a spoon to help drizzle jelly over almond fingers."],"basicInfo":["medium","40m","2h","46 pieces"]}